PURE CONNECTION was allowed to settled along the inside, saved ground well behind the group on the backstretch, then was gaining on the far turn to rally in the upper stretch, then dueled with the pace setter in late stretch and hung in the end. LADLE chased the pace while in the two path throughout the first half, then bid gamely on the far turn in the early stretch, could not find room between the vying leaders, angled in towards the rail then continued to bid with what was left but it was not enough. EURCOOL broke outwardly at the start, gained the brief lead into the first turn then settled back along the inside down the backstretch then continued to flattened out throughout the second half. STRANGE JOY chased the early while three wide in the middle of the pack then settled back and was no menace. FOXY ELAINE settled along the inside and was thru after the half.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 6 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. ZIPPIN PIPPIN battled with inner rivals from the four path into the early backstretch, then gained the lead heading into the far turn, held on gamely in the early stretch but was met by an incoming rival on the outside and was out finished in the end. SAY SAYONARA tracked the pace in the two path in the middle of the pack down the backstretch, then was gaining ground on the far turn to attempt to gain the lead in the early stretch but could not and was best for the show prize. PINK ROBE chased the pace in the middle of the field while being rated on the backstretch, then rallied on the far turn and into the home stretch but came up empty. STUPENDOUS vied for the lead in the three path and between rivals, then continued to bid in close behind the leader throughout the far turn before giving way in the home stretch. AIRFORCE ANNIE vied for the lead from the inside into the first turn and down the backstretch, then continued to press the pace throughout the far turn under a hard drive, was used up and stopped in the stretch. BLUE BLUE BAYOU raced from the inside in the back group down the backstretch, then bid while two wide on the far turn and was no threat. ENGLISH ROSE broke outwardly at the start, then trailed behind the field and passed tired rivals in the second half of the course. MURIELLE settled in the two path in the third group of contenders then continued to lose ground and was no factor. TAMARAC LADY vied for the lead early between rivals then was thru after the three eighths marker.
